# Core Project Directory Rules

## Project Structure Schema
```
core/
├── back-end/           # Python backend services
│   ├── api/           # API endpoints and handlers
│   ├── database/      # Data storage and management
│   │   └── data/      # CSV files, images, text data
│   ├── logic/         # Business logic modules
│   │   ├── embedings/ # ML embeddings (parquet files)
│   │   ├── image/     # Image processing (OCR, scraping)
│   │   └── text/      # Text analysis (MeCab, NLP)
│   └── server/        # Server configuration and deployment
├── front-end/         # JavaScript frontend (ES6 modules)
│   ├── index.html     # Main HTML entry point
│   ├── main.js        # Application entry point
│   ├── recognition.js # Speech recognition logic
│   ├── translation.js # Translation API calls
│   ├── ui.js          # DOM manipulation and UI updates
│   ├── utils.js       # Utility functions
│   └── vocabulary.js  # Vocabulary management and coverage
└── mobile/           # iOS Swift application
    └── ios/          # Xcode project and Swift code
```

## Coding Standards
- Functions must be under 20 lines
- Functions must have at most 1 input and 1 output
- No comments in code
- Use ES6 modules for frontend
- Use Python type hints for backend
- Follow single responsibility principle

## Technology Stack
- Frontend: Vanilla JavaScript (ES6 modules)
- Backend: Python HTTP server + WebSocket
- Mobile: Swift/iOS
- Data: CSV files, Parquet embeddings
- Hosting: Cloudflare Tunnel
